names.details: Nehr-i Tān: It is a great river, which is opposite the River Özü (the Dnieper) and to the west of the River Itil (the Volga). Everybody knows that it flows to the Sea of Azov. (translated from Ottoman Turkish to English by the first creator of this entry.)
